A Note to this: It has come to my attention that I am not the only person that needs to go to Fear in order to do progress on their epic. Enchanters and Wizzys alike need to mash around this place and get some drops. So, even though i am not up to this point, even though nothing is required (as far as turn ins etc) to go to fear. WTB FEAR RAID<br>
<br>
OK, all the easy beans done on this thing... now i just have to do the hard stuff and get my true spirit faction to max ally and I will be good to go on epic for senor shaman.<br>
1) High Scale Kirn: ok need some people on this one Guide suggests 3 groups of 60's... i dunno. Anyway, we have to pretty much lay waste to most of the zone so that we can get to the High Scale Kirn, i hand in the iron that i got in the previous quest, then he kills me... or i somehow get out of the way before he eats me and we destroy him, he drops a ring and we all go home.<br>
2) The Final Steps: OK ill break this up in several parts to make it organized:<br>
a) in COM I need to hand that ring into Neh`Ashiir, to get this to spawn, the group/groups of people that i go with need to kill Black Reavers which are about 100% magic resistant.. so tanks a pleanty would be butta. She drops a diary which i hand into a spirit in EJ.<br>
b) POF to kill either Dread, Fright, or Terror after you kill one of them an iksar broodling will spawn. I kill him (he is lvl 1) and loot his tear.<br>
c) back to COM to hand that tear into Lord Rak`Ashiir, as soon as that turn in is completed, he goes nuts and tries to kill me.<br>
d) after that go kill Lord Rak`Ashiir again (might be a problem with the guide) but he will drop an iksar scale... and there you have it... a few hand ins and i get the spear of fate... TADA<br>
(ANYONE WHO HAS ANY SUGGESTIONS PLZ POST THEM HERE, i will be checking periodically and updating with my progress)<br>
-Ophidion<br>
